      • autoID

        public void autoID()
        This method automatically generates an ID for a customer before they are added to the system.

        First, the method establishes a connection with the 'airline' database to look at the customer table. It uses a query to select the highest ID value saved in the database. If the customer table within the 'airline' database is completely empty, then this method will assign the next created customer object to have the staring ID, CS001. By grabbing the highest ID value each time and incrementing it, the system prevents two customers from having identical IDs. This also means the user is unable to tamper with ID values while running the program.

      • jButton1ActionPerformed

        private void jButton1ActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
        This method is tied to the "Browse" button on the 'Add Customer' screen accessed from Main.java

        It opens a file input stream and then asks for the user to select a valid image file. The valid image file extensions are png, jpg, and .images type files. After a user has selected a valid image file from their device, the system reads the image path and sets the customer's photo to look through that path. When this is complete, the GUI will refresh and show the user the selected image within the 'Add Customer' screen. At the same time the userimage swing attribute is set to the path which was provided by the user to the image. This is a required step for the addition of a customer into the database.

        Parameters:
        evt - Whenever the "Browse" button is clicked, this method is called

      • jButton2ActionPerformed

        private void jButton2ActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
        This method is tied to the "Add" button on the 'Add Customer' screen accessed from Main.java

        If a user has filled out all of the text boxes, date pickers, and selected a valid image for a customer object, then this method will add a new customer object with the provided values. A connection to the database is required for this function to work.

        Parameters:
        evt - Whenever the "Add" button is clicked this method is called
